CRM stands for Customer Relationship Management. It is a system or software that helps businesses manage their relationships and interactions with customers.
In simple words, CRM acts like a smart digital notebook where a company stores customer information such as:
Contact details
Purchase history
Customer questions or complaints
Follow-up reminders
Sales and communication records
Instead of employees trying to remember everything manually, the CRM keeps all customer information organized in one place.
For example, imagine you own an online store. A customer asks about a product today and calls again next week. With a CRM, you can quickly see their previous conversation, what they purchased, and what support they need. This helps you respond faster and give a more personal experience.
CRM helps businesses:
Build stronger customer relationships
Improve customer service
Track sales opnortunities
